'''Maximilian Michael Arfsten''' (born April 19, 2001) is an American professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Columbus Crew]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].

== Early years ==
=== Youth ===
Arfsten attended [[San Joaquin Memorial High School]]. In 2016, he posted 21 goals, 11 assists and earned all-league first team honors. He ended his junior season with All-CMAC first team recognition and league MVP honors by posting 20 goals and 21 assists. He helped the team win the league and Central Section championships that year, also earning all-league first team honors for the third straight season, and captured league MVP accolades for the second year in a row after ending his final season with 50 goals and 20 assists.<ref name=":1" /> Arfsten also played club soccer with local side California Odyssey for nine years, where he was the leading National Premier League goal scorer.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://ucdavisaggies.com/sports/mens-soccer/roster/maximilian-arfsten/9665|title=Maximilian Arfsten - Men's Soccer|website=UC Davis Athletics}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.californiaodyssey.org/alumni|title=General 2|website=California Odyssey Soccer Club}}</ref>

=== College ===
In 2019, Arfsten attended the [[University of California, Davis]] to play [[college soccer]]. Between 2019 and 2021, he made 39 appearances for the Aggies, scoring nine goals and tallying eight assists. He earned [[Big West Conference]] All-Freshman Team honors in 2019. His sophomore season was canceled due to [[COVID-19]], and just ahead of his junior season, he broke his foot and was out for five months.<ref name=":1" /> He was named Big West Offensive Player of the Year and All-Big West First Team in 2021.<ref name="auto"/><ref>{{Cite web |last=Spencer |first=Jason |date=2021-11-12 |title=Arfsten, Mejia take home top Big West honors |url=https://ucdavisaggies.com/story.aspx?filename=mens-soccer-arfsten-mejia-take-home-top-big-west-honors&file_date=11-12-2021 |access-date=2024-07-09 |website=UC Davis Athletics |language=en}}</ref> Prior to the 2022 season, Arfsten opted to leave college early and play professionally.

== Club career ==
===San Jose Earthquakes II===
In 2022, he signed his first contract with [[MLS Next Pro]] side [[San Jose Earthquakes II]] ahead of their inaugural season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sjearthquakes.com/earthquakesii/news/news-earthquakes-announce-second-team-roster|title=NEWS: Earthquakes Announce Quakes II Roster &#124; RSL Monarchs|website=sjearthquakes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sjearthquakes.com/earthquakesii/news/quakes-ii-preview-pacific-division-team-introductions|title=QUAKES II PREVIEW: Pacific Division Team Introductions &#124; RSL Monarchs|website=sjearthquakes}}</ref> In his lone season with the Quakes reserve team, Arfsten scored nine goals in 24 appearances.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlsnextpro.com/players/maximilian-arfsten/stats/|title=Max Arfsten &#124; MLSsoccer.com|website=mlsnextpro}}</ref>

===Columbus Crew===

==== 2023 ====
In December 2022, Arfsten was announced as eligible for selection in the [[2023 MLS SuperDraft]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/mls-superdraft-2023-presented-by-adidas-eligible-player-list|title=MLS SuperDraft 2023 eligible players &#124; MLSSoccer.com|website=mlssoccer}}</ref> He was selected 14th overall by the [[Columbus Crew]] on December 21, 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bigwest.org/news/2022/12/21/mens-soccer-former-aggie-maximilian-arfsten-selected-14th-overall-in-2023-mls-superdraft.aspx|title=Former Aggie Maximilian Arfsten Selected 14th Overall in 2023 MLS SuperDraft|website=bigwest.org|date=December 20, 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.massivereport.com/2022/12/21/23521783/mls-superdraft-2023-columbus-crew-select-maximilian-arfsten-no-14-overall|title=MLS SuperDraft 2023: The Crew select Maximilian Arfsten No. 14 overall|date=December 21, 2022|website=Massive Report}}{{Dead link|date=February 2026 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.columbuscrew.com/news/columbus-crew-selects-three-players-in-2023-mls-superdraft-presented-by-adidas|title=Columbus Crew Selects Three Players in 2023 MLS SuperDraft Presented by Adidas &#124; Columbus Crew|website=ColumbusCrew.com}}</ref> He signed a two-year deal with the [[Major League Soccer]] side on February 21, 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.columbuscrew.com/news/columbus-crew-signs-mls-superdraft-pick-maximilian-max-arfsten|title=Columbus Crew signs MLS SuperDraft pick Maximilian "Max" Arfsten &#124; Columbus Crew|website=ColumbusCrew.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ucdavisaggies.com/news/2023/2/21/mens-soccer-arfsten-signs-with-columbus-crew.aspx|title=Arfsten Signs With Columbus Crew|website=UC Davis Athletics|date=February 21, 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2023/02/21/columbus-crew-sign-superdraft-pick-max-arfsten-to-two-year-contract/69925691007/|title=Columbus Crew sign 2023 SuperDraft first round pick Max Arfsten to two-year contract|website=The Columbus Dispatch}}</ref> Arfsten made his debut and scored his first goal for Columbus on March 25, 2023, in a 6–1 victory over [[Atlanta United FC|Atlanta United]] after coming on as a late substitute.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gay |first=Colin |date=2023-03-25 |title=New-look Columbus Crew rolls through Atlanta United for 6-1 home win |url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2023/03/25/columbus-crew-rolls-through-atlanta-united-with-6-1-win/70048216007/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230326051622/https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2023/03/25/columbus-crew-rolls-through-atlanta-united-with-6-1-win/70048216007/ |archive-date=2023-03-26 |access-date=2023-03-26 |website=The Columbus Dispatch |language=en-US}}</ref> He made his first start on June 3, replacing [[Mohamed Farsi]] in the starting lineup after the wing-back was injured during warmups. Playing on the right side, Arfsten scored and assisted in the 4–2 win against [[Charlotte FC]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Johnson |first=Bailey |date=June 4, 2023 |title='We are growing': Takeaways and analysis from the Crew's 4-2 win over Charlotte FC |url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2023/06/04/takeaways-analysis-columbus-crew-beat-charlotte-fc-4-2/70279792007/ |website=The Columbus Dispatch}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Fisher |first=Tyler |date=2023-06-04 |title=Christian Ramirez brace leads to Crew's 4-2 win vs. Charlotte FC |url=https://massive-report.com/2023/06/03/christian-ramirez-brace-leads-to-columbus-crews-4-2-win-vs-charlotte-fc-mls-2023/ |access-date=2026-03-21 |website=Massive Report |language=en}}</ref> During the 2023 playoffs, he scored in the only match he appeared in as his side would go on to win the [[MLS Cup 2023|MLS Cup]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Max Arfsten 2023 Match Logs |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/668f881e/matchlogs/2023/Max-Arfsten-Match-Logs |access-date=2025-06-23 |website=FBref.com |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2024 ====
During the 2024 season, Arfsten entrenched himself as the starting left [[Wing back (association football)|wing-back]] in a [[Formation (association football)#3–5–2|3–5–2 formation]]. He made his [[CONCACAF Champions Cup]] debut off the bench on March 6, 2024 in a 1–0 win for the Crew against the [[Houston Dynamo FC|Houston Dynamo]] in the round-of-16. On April 9, Arfsten took the final penalty in the shootout win versus [[Tigres UANL]] at [[Estadio Universitario (UANL)|Estadio Universitario]] to send Columbus to the semifinals of the Champions Cup.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Benatar |first=Orri |date=2024-04-10 |title=Crew make first CONCACAF semifinals after beating Tigres on penalties |url=https://www.nbc4i.com/sports/mls/columbus-crew/crew-make-first-concacaf-semifinals-after-beating-tigres-on-penalties/ |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20250109171224/https://www.nbc4i.com/sports/mls/columbus-crew/crew-make-first-concacaf-semifinals-after-beating-tigres-on-penalties/ |archive-date=2025-01-09 |access-date=2026-05-27 |work=NBC4 WCMH-TV |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=April 10, 2024 |title=Patrick Schulte heroics push Columbus Crew to historic upset of Tigres UANL {{!}} MLSSoccer.com |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/patrick-schulte-heroics-power-columbus-crew-in-ccc-upset-of-tigres-uanl |access-date=2026-05-27 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref> He scored in back-to-back league games on May 11 and May 15.<ref name=":3" /> During the [[2024 Leagues Cup]], Arfsten started all five games as his club won the tournament. On September 21, he had two assists in the match against [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]], with the first assist coming with his left foot while the second came from his right.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=Max Arfsten 2024 Match Logs |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/668f881e/matchlogs/2024/Max-Arfsten-Match-Logs |access-date=2025-06-23 |website=FBref.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bbFufk8QrjA|title=Columbus Crew vs. Orlando City <nowiki>|</nowiki> 7 Goal Battle! <nowiki>|</nowiki> Full Match Highlights|date=Sep 21, 2024|type=Video|language=English|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260130202708/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bbFufk8QrjA|archive-date=January 30, 2026|url-status=live|publisher=Major League Soccer}}</ref> On October 16, it was announced that Arfsten had signed a contract extension until 2027, with a club option for 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=Oct 16, 2024 |title=Columbus Crew sign Max Arfsten to multi-year contract extension |url=https://www.columbuscrew.com/news/columbus-crew-sign-max-arfsten-to-multi-year-contract-extension |access-date=2025-06-23 |website=ColumbusCrew.com |language=en}}</ref> 

==== 2025 ====
Arfsten scored his first goal in 2025 against expansion side [[San Diego FC]], in a 1–1 draw at [[Snapdragon Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=2025 Max Arfsten Match Logs |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/668f881e/matchlogs/2025/Max-Arfsten-Match-Logs |access-date=2026-05-27 |website=FBref.com |language=en}}</ref> 

== International career ==
[[File:Maximilian Arfsten, 2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup, 03 (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|250px|Arfsten with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in 2025.]]

On January 6, 2025, Arfsten was called up to the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]] by head coach [[Mauricio Pochettino]] ahead of the January camp in Florida, with friendlies against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] and [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Twenty-Four Players Called for First USMNT January Training Camp Under Mauricio Pochettino |url=https://ussoccer.com/stories/2025/01/twenty-four-players-called-for-first-usmnt-january-training-camp-under-mauricio-pochettino |access-date=2026-05-11 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref> Arfsten made his debut on January 18, 2025 versus Venezuela.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USMNT vs. Venezuela: Starting XI & Lineup Notes |url=https://ussoccer.com/stories/2025/01/us-mens-national-team-vs-venezuela-usa-lineup-today-starting-11-squad-lineup-notes |access-date=2026-05-11 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref> Arfsten netted his first career international goal in the semifinals of the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] against [[Panama national football team|Panama]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=U.S. Men's National Team Advances to Gold Cup Semifinals with Win over Costa Rica in Penalty Kicks |url=https://ussoccer.com/stories/2025/06/usmnt-costa-rica-concacaf-gold-cup-quarterfinals-recap-highlights-matt-freese-diego-luna |access-date=2026-05-11 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref> He played significant minutes in the tournament, starting in all but one game for the U.S., as they finished runner-up in the competition to [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=From A to Z: Arfsten, Zendejas Combine to Score Opening Goal for USMNT |url=https://ussoccer.com/stories/2025/09/max-arfsten-alex-zendejas-combine-to-score-opening-goal-usmnt-vs-japan |access-date=2026-05-11 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
[[File:Max Arfsten USMNT v Belgium Mar 28 2026-221.jpg|thumb|275px|right|Arfsten (left) in a match against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]].]]

A [[Footedness|two-footed]] player, Arfsten has been noted for his bravery, technical ability, and penchant for taking players on via the dribble.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=USMNT roster prediction: Who could make January 2025 camp? |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/usmnt-roster-prediction-who-could-make-january-2025-camp |access-date=2026-05-11 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref> He has described himself as a player that "like[s] to dribble a lot and be shifty as much as I can, just to create chances, so I think my aggressiveness in my attack sets me apart."<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Romo |first=Vanessa |date=2022-03-21 |title=Fresno native Max Arfsten signs to San Jose Earthquakes |url=https://kmph.com/sports/content/fresno-native-max-arfsten-signs-to-san-jose-earthquakes |access-date=2025-07-10 |website=KMPH |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Doyle |first=Matthew |date=Dec 18, 2024 |title=USMNT roster prediction: Who could make January 2025 camp? |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/usmnt-roster-prediction-who-could-make-january-2025-camp |access-date=2025-07-10 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Arfsten has stated that his soccer inspiration is [[Neymar]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Renkel |first=Favian |date=2025-06-05 |title=Max Arfsten's Rise: From MLS NEXT Pro Pioneer to USMNT Mainstay |url=https://urbanpitch.com/max-arfstens-rise-from-mls-next-pro-pioneer-to-usmnt-mainstay/ |access-date=2025-06-23 |website=Urban Pitch |language=en-US}}</ref>

